<TITLE> 1 dead in Rangamati shoot out </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangamati, May 2 (bdnews24.com)  One person was killed on Sunday in Rangamati as two armed groups had a gun battle. Proshanto Chakma, from Labour Para, was a member of the United People's Democratic Front (UPDF) and the office secretary of the Jurachhari Upazila Gonotantrik Jubo Forum, a wing of the UPDF. UPDF has accused the Parbattya Chattagram Janasanghati Samity (PCJSS) for the killing. Abu Ali Md Sajjad Hossain, Upazila Nirbahi Officer of Jurachhari told reporters that a group of PCJSS members attacked a group of UPDF activists. Proshanto was killed in the spot during the ensuing gun battle, he said. Sajjad told bdnews24.com that the law and order situation in the upazila was under control. Michael Chakma, member secretary of central Gonotantrik Jubo Forum has accused the PCJSS for the killing. Sajib Chakma, assistant information and publicity secretary of PCJSS said that he did not know anything about the incident. bdnews24.co
